  "title": "Scaffold Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>The Scaffold Supervisor is responsible for planning, supervising, and ensuring the safe erection, modification, and dismantling of scaffolding structures at construction or industrial sites. The role involves leading a team of scaffolders, conducting safety inspections, and ensuring all scaffolding works comply with statutory and safety standards.<br /></p><p>Key Responsibilities:<br /></p><p>Supervise and coordinate daily scaffolding activities at the worksite.<br /></p><p>Plan scaffolding requirements according to project needs and drawings.<br /></p><p>Inspect scaffolding materials and structures to ensure safety and compliance with regulations (SS659 / WSH standards).<br /></p><p>Verify scaffold tags and ensure scaffolds are safe for use before work begins.<br /></p><p>Conduct toolbox meetings and brief workers on safety requirements.<br /></p><p>Ensure workers follow proper scaffolding procedures and use PPE.<br /></p><p>Liaise with site engineers, safety officers, and project managers regarding scaffold access requirements.<br /></p><p>Maintain records of scaffold inspections, permits, and maintenance.<br /></p><p>Identify and report hazards or unsafe practices immediately.<br /></p><p>Train and mentor scaffold erectors and riggers under supervision.<br /></p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
